entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am someone who sleeps in late so i always get at least six or seven hours if i have to wake up early for something i get nauseous sometimes i will throw up in the morning yeah i have had jobs where i would wake up and you know vomit while i am brushing my teeth it is horrible

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sucks

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it does suck it is kinda something i am worried about you know i i kinda need to get some part time work while i am not you know getting a steady pay flow for my music production so yeah it is pretty rough got some stuff i need to get over i am not really sure how

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: like what

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just not feeling good getting nervous when you know there is something stressful like a stressful work environment or just something i that does not sit well with me like being in a you know a a rushed and you know stressful work environment it just unless it is about something that i care about you know like music or the arts it is just very hard to to give a shit frankly like and you know i i try to psych myself into giving a shit and it just makes me sick you know maybe i will have a red bull or something and you know xxx my body does not want that in the morning it just i feel like my body rejects things and yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: okay i have been feeling okay very very reflective very contemplative you know there is gonna be some changes and there is gonna be some new people in my life some new people in my band you know i am gonna try to push myself but try to stay grounded at the same time cause you know i expect more from myself it is just pissing me off when my get my you know i basically feel like i am shitting all over myself my body is shitting on me anyway just by being so shitty yeah

entries.text: i was diagnosed about twelve years ago i have not been in therapy since they gave me zoloft and i did not like it

entries.text: it made me feel worse than i do in the shittiest moments i was telling you about it it it made me feel nb i do not wanna feel nb i wanna feel everything even if it sucks

entries.text: i understand what got you to seek help

entries.text: being forced to it was a private school they thought i was acting up thought i was a uppity kid i think i was just being a kid so
